  "6d26932f-1c29-4368-9fef-84d73228c942"],
 "\n     But... Mathematica now considers all of these symbols to be \
constants\n     For less complicated expressions, Mathematica erroneously \
performs the integral accordingly\n          If that happens, just omit \
/.rulesDisp. The simpler expressions should be almost as readable\n          \
For example,  ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubsuperscriptBox["\[Integral]", "1", "r"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "ba9953df-628d-4140-90ec-a944d000fbf4"],
