     RowBox[{
     "Print", "[", "\"\<\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(R\), \
\(11\)]\)-2\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(R\), \(22\)]\)-\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(R\), \(44\
\)]\) eliminates both double deriviatives, and we can solve it for \
\[GothicCapitalD] (but not for \[GothicCapitalC]). The solution for \
\[GothicCapitalD] involves an integral involving various \[GothicCapitalD](r) \
and a(t) terms. Plugging back in, \!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(R\), \(11\)]\) and \
\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(R\), \(44\)]\) are unwieldy but the resulting \
\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(R\), \(22\)]\) is reasonably compact and has no integral \
terms. Nonetheless, I was unable to solve it for \[GothicCapitalC]. \>\"", 
      "]"}], ";", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
     RowBox[{"Print", "[", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(R\), \
\(11\)]\)-2\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(R\), \(22\)]\)-\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(R\), \(44\
\)]\):  \>\"", ",", 
       RowBox[{"lhs124", "/.", "rulesDisp"}], ",", 
       RowBox[{"\"\< = \>\"", "rhs124"}]}], "]"}], ";", "\[IndentingNewLine]",
      "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
     RowBox[{"Print", "[", "]"}], ";", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
     RowBox[{
     "Print", "[", "\"\<Also, plugging in the formula for a(t) makes things \
worse, not better.\>\"", "]"}], ";", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
     "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
     RowBox[{"Print", "[", "]"}], ";", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
